01:13:21,480 --> 01:13:24,484
I'm gonna tell you the truth. I knew
damn well you wouldn't do the gig.

973
01:13:25,320 --> 01:13:29,086
That's the first thing that came out
your mouth that wasn't a fucking lie.

974
01:13:30,680 --> 01:13:32,205
What the hell? That's him!

975
01:13:36,280 --> 01:13:39,284
- Get him, he's unarmed.
- Careful, behind there.

976
01:13:39,480 --> 01:13:41,721
- Behind there, go.
- There he is, there he is!

977
01:13:42,880 --> 01:13:44,370
He's got my gun.

978
01:13:45,560 --> 01:13:48,803
- There, in the corner!
- Not me, damn it.

979
01:13:50,040 --> 01:13:51,485
You son of a bitch!

980
01:13:58,040 --> 01:13:59,610
Brooks!

981
01:14:04,800 --> 01:14:06,165
He's out the door.

982
01:14:06,360 --> 01:14:08,886
Connors, get him! Kill the bastard.

983
01:14:09,080 --> 01:14:11,208
Shut your ass up.

984
01:14:19,960 --> 01:14:21,291
Brooks.

985
01:14:37,960 --> 01:14:39,246
Brooks!

986
01:14:39,440 --> 01:14:41,442
Drop the gun. Drop it!

987
01:14:42,200 --> 01:14:44,089
Drop it, drop it.

988
01:14:46,640 --> 01:14:48,324
And the bomb.

989
01:14:50,520 --> 01:14:51,885
Step away.

990
01:14:55,640 --> 01:14:57,165
Can't we talk this out, partner?

991
01:14:57,920 --> 01:15:01,049
I mean, you're forgetting I let you go.

992
01:15:01,800 --> 01:15:04,804
Even left you
that pretty bitch to help you out.

993
01:15:05,640 --> 01:15:07,927
Now, if I wanted to kill you...

994
01:15:08,120 --> 01:15:10,805
...I would have done it
right then and there.

995
01:15:11,000 --> 01:15:14,163
That's the only reason you ain't got
a bullet in your ass right now.

996
01:15:14,360 --> 01:15:16,283
See, you ain't nothing
but a common murderer.

997
01:15:16,760 --> 01:15:18,250
Stone-cold killer, huh?

998
01:15:19,320 --> 01:15:22,369
You killed Dr. Mackenzie
and his assistant...

999
01:15:22,560 --> 01:15:24,050
...for what?

1000
01:15:29,120 --> 01:15:30,804
It had to be done.

1001
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:33,287
You know how it works,
you gotta tie up the loose ends.

1002
01:15:34,240 --> 01:15:38,165
Look, this government
was gonna kill me.

1003
01:15:38,360 --> 01:15:41,523
I don't give a fuck if it's
the president or the pope...

1004
01:15:41,720 --> 01:15:43,165
...or who the fuck else.

1005
01:15:43,720 --> 01:15:47,441
I ain't hardly sitting around
waiting for somebody to off me.

1006
01:15:47,640 --> 01:15:50,883
Mama Brooks didn't raise
no stupid-ass children.

1007
01:16:01,800 --> 01:16:03,040
Oh, there's my ride.

1008
01:16:04,040 --> 01:16:06,520
All I gotta do is signal for pickup...

1009
01:16:06,720 --> 01:16:08,961
...break the seal on the CMC...

1010
01:16:09,160 --> 01:16:11,401
...and in five minutes, I'm free.

1011
01:16:12,600 --> 01:16:14,602
Well, look, you could come with me.

1012
01:16:14,800 --> 01:16:17,610
We could head for
the Grand Cayman islands.

1013
01:16:17,800 --> 01:16:19,529
Break open my piggy bank.

1014
01:16:20,120 --> 01:16:23,283
Start spending
that 100 mil I been stacking.

1015
01:16:23,480 --> 01:16:25,801
No! No more of your fucking lies!

1016
01:16:26,000 --> 01:16:29,527
We could get your eyes right.
That's the first thing we'll do, dog.

1017
01:16:29,720 --> 01:16:31,404
Permanent.

1018
01:16:33,680 --> 01:16:35,409
You gotta make
a decision here, partner.

1019
01:16:36,880 --> 01:16:38,928
You wanna be a blind old man...

1020
01:16:39,120 --> 01:16:41,885
...sitting out the rest of your days
on your back porch...

1021
01:16:42,080 --> 01:16:44,606
...in the fog, getting sauced?

1022
01:16:44,800 --> 01:16:46,689
Or you wanna be somebody again?

1023
01:16:46,880 --> 01:16:49,770
No! It's over, shut up!

1024
01:16:54,760 --> 01:16:56,364
Marco.

1025
01:16:58,160 --> 01:17:00,242
You're supposed to say Polo.

1026
01:17:02,520 --> 01:17:03,965
Don't play fucking games, right?

1027
01:17:06,840 --> 01:17:08,922
Brooks, do not fucking move.

1028
01:17:11,600 --> 01:17:13,364
Billy!

1029
01:17:14,400 --> 01:17:16,004
Brooks!

1030
01:17:22,440 --> 01:17:24,010
Brooks!

1031
01:17:42,840 --> 01:17:44,604
Polo.

1032
01:17:59,640 --> 01:18:02,928
<i>It's in locker number 605,
it's kept on ice.</i>

1033
01:19:36,040 --> 01:19:38,088
Howard, what?

1034
01:19:38,280 --> 01:19:42,285
That's impossible. I had my hand
over my mouth the entire time.

1035
01:19:42,480 --> 01:19:44,323
- What's the trick?
- Ain't no trick.

1036
01:19:44,520 --> 01:19:46,761
Of course there's a trick.

1037
01:19:46,960 --> 01:19:49,042
- There's gotta be.
- Okay.

1038
01:19:49,240 --> 01:19:51,481
- You got me, there is a trick.
- What?

1039
01:19:51,680 --> 01:19:54,047
You're the only pain in the ass
that comes and visit me.

1040
01:19:55,160 --> 01:19:56,924
- That's it?
- That's it.

1041
01:19:57,120 --> 01:19:58,531
Now, what do you want?

1042
01:19:59,240 --> 01:20:02,642
My transmission is fucked.
My clutch is mush.

1043
01:20:02,840 --> 01:20:05,241
- So?
- So before you took my classic...

1044
01:20:05,440 --> 01:20:08,444
...on your little joy ride,
she was virgin tight.

1045
01:20:08,640 --> 01:20:11,007
- It's gonna cost me money.
- I knew it was coming.

1046
01:20:11,200 --> 01:20:13,282
- How much?
- About a grand.

1047
01:20:13,480 --> 01:20:15,687
Bullshit. That whole truck
ain't worth a grand.

1048
01:20:15,880 --> 01:20:18,929
All right, 250,
if I get Debbie to do the work.

1049
01:20:19,120 --> 01:20:21,805
And you're never, never gonna
borrow my ride again.

1050
01:20:22,000 --> 01:20:23,684
Whatever, I'll give you
a check tomorrow.

1051
01:20:23,880 --> 01:20:25,530
You better.

1052
01:20:25,720 --> 01:20:27,802
- Hey, Howard?
- Yeah?

1053
01:20:28,000 --> 01:20:29,161
What are you doing later?

1054
01:20:29,680 --> 01:20:31,762
You and Debbie wanna come over,
have some grub?

1055
01:20:33,200 --> 01:20:34,531
With you?

1056
01:20:36,880 --> 01:20:39,804
Hey, this is a first.
What's the occasion?

1057
01:20:40,000 --> 01:20:41,570
It's no occasion, it's just dinner.

1058
01:20:42,760 --> 01:20:45,730
- Sounds great. What are we having?
- We having steak.

1059
01:20:46,520 --> 01:20:49,888
Oh, no, no. Absolutely not.

1060
01:20:50,200 --> 01:20:54,444
Red meat? Now I know
where you get all this aggression.

1061
01:20:54,640 --> 01:20:56,210
Red meat.

1062
01:20:56,400 --> 01:20:59,165
Fuck, no wonder you got
the Man shooting at you.

1063
01:20:59,360 --> 01:21:01,362
You're bringing trouble
into your neighbourhood.

1064
01:21:01,560 --> 01:21:06,771
It's the whole bad karma, red meat,
military-industrial complex...

1065
01:21:06,960 --> 01:21:09,042
-...macho-fantasy bullshit.
- Okay.

1066
01:21:11,440 --> 01:21:13,204
More for us.

1067
01:21:18,680 --> 01:21:20,409
Shit.

1068
01:21:22,040 --> 01:21:23,769
What you doing,
lighting up the barbecue...

1069
01:21:23,960 --> 01:21:25,291
...or burning down my yacht?

1070
01:21:25,480 --> 01:21:28,802
I'm not burning anything,
I can't get the charcoals lit.

1071
01:21:29,160 --> 01:21:31,083
You know, might
have to go inside.

1072
01:21:31,280 --> 01:21:33,203
You know, with that
cooking skills of yours...

1073
01:21:33,400 --> 01:21:35,164
...you gonna make
a lucky man real happy.

1074
01:21:35,360 --> 01:21:36,885
All right, shut up.

1075
01:21:37,080 --> 01:21:38,491
Thank you.

1076
01:21:38,680 --> 01:21:40,205
Look, I'm only kidding.

1077
01:21:40,400 --> 01:21:43,483
Why don't you come over here
and sit down. Take a load off, mama.

1078
01:21:43,680 --> 01:21:45,409
I'm all over that.

1079
01:21:49,120 --> 01:21:51,282
- Here, baby, take that.
- Thank you.

1080
01:21:52,040 --> 01:21:53,769
How's about a little toast?

1081
01:21:53,960 --> 01:21:56,361
You know, actually we have
nothing to toast about.

1082
01:21:56,560 --> 01:21:58,927
- I mean, neither one of us has a job.
- True.

1083
01:21:59,120 --> 01:22:00,929
- Both of our bosses are dead.
- As doorknobs.

1084
01:22:01,120 --> 01:22:03,088
- You killed yours.
- Hey, it was self-defence.

1085
01:22:03,280 --> 01:22:05,726
Greene is back at his cushy job.

1086
01:22:05,920 --> 01:22:09,242
Swept everything under the carpet like
the last two days never even existed.

1087
01:22:09,440 --> 01:22:12,649
- That's the way the government do.
- There's no funds for the research.

1088
01:22:12,840 --> 01:22:14,729
No serum.

1089
01:22:15,120 --> 01:22:17,122
- And you're still blind.
- As a bat.

1090
01:22:17,320 --> 01:22:19,971
- So see, there's nothing to toast to.
- I disagree.

1091
01:22:22,160 --> 01:22:23,844
All right, so,
what is there to toast to?

1092
01:22:24,360 --> 01:22:26,169
Well, I think...

1093
01:22:26,360 --> 01:22:28,567
...that we need to toast...

1094
01:22:28,960 --> 01:22:30,121
...to our friendship.

1095
01:22:31,840 --> 01:22:33,365
To our friendship.

1096
01:22:35,320 --> 01:22:37,004
Connors, if you go
Mr. Rogers on me...

1097
01:22:37,200 --> 01:22:40,522
-...I'm gonna throw myself off this boat.
- Don't do that, I need you.

1098
01:22:41,840 --> 01:22:45,925
All right, so, what, you've got
some kind of a friendship toast?

1099
01:22:46,120 --> 01:22:48,646
- Matter of fact, I do.
- Of course.

1100
01:22:48,840 --> 01:22:51,730
One of my O.G. killer soldiers
taught it to me...

1101
01:22:51,920 --> 01:22:53,490
...while we was together on the brig.

1102
01:22:54,120 --> 01:22:56,202
While you was on the brig?

1103
01:22:56,400 --> 01:22:58,402
- All right, let's hear it.
- All right.

1104
01:22:59,160 --> 01:23:00,730
Here's to you...

1105
01:23:00,920 --> 01:23:02,160
...and here's to me.

1106
01:23:03,120 --> 01:23:04,610
And friends we shall be...

1107
01:23:05,640 --> 01:23:06,880
...till eternity.

1108
01:23:07,960 --> 01:23:10,008
And if we ever disagree...

1109
01:23:10,200 --> 01:23:12,009
...fuck you, and here's to me.

1110
01:23:14,240 --> 01:23:16,004
That is retarded.

1111
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:18,965
I know, but you laughed
and you toasted.

1112
01:23:19,160 --> 01:23:20,321
You're right about that.

1113
01:23:24,080 --> 01:23:26,048
God, it's freezing out here.

1114
01:23:26,240 --> 01:23:27,810
Nice day for a barbeque.

1115
01:23:28,280 --> 01:23:30,282
Know what, I know someplace
that's not cold.

1116
01:23:30,480 --> 01:23:31,891
Yeah, me too. Hawaii.

1117
01:23:32,560 --> 01:23:35,404
I was thinking more of the lines
of the Cayman islands.

1118
01:23:35,600 --> 01:23:37,728
Cayman islands.
Name me one good reason...

1119
01:23:37,920 --> 01:23:40,890
...to go to the Caymans
instead of Hawaii.

1120
01:23:41,080 --> 01:23:43,367
I got a hundred million
good reasons to go.

1121
01:23:43,560 --> 01:23:44,846
A hundred million reasons?

1122
01:23:45,040 --> 01:23:46,280
All right, name me one.

1123
01:23:46,840 --> 01:23:50,128
Two first-class tickets
with our names on them.

1124
01:23:50,640 --> 01:23:53,803
- You're full of shit.
- I ain't lying.